FBIS4-54928 "dreeu088_p_94004" FBIS-EEU-94-088 Daily Report 5 May 1994 POLAND Pawlak Confers With U.S. Trade Secretary Brown Pawlak Confers With U.S. Trade Secretary Brown LD0505184894 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1642 GMT 5 May 94 LD0505184894 Warsaw PAP Polish BFN [Text] Warsaw, 5 May--Following today's meeting with U.S. Trade Secretary Ronald Brown, Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak said that he hopes better conditions for full economic cooperation between Poland and the United States will be created. The prime minister stressed that the best way for meeting Poland's obligations toward the United States is the development of trade between the two countries. Brown described the talk with the prime minister as constructive. "We spoke about how trade and investment cooperation between Poland and the United States could be expanded," he said.
